reviews.review: True Star Wars. Epic, heart-pounding, tear-hjerking, high-flying adventure. Will rewatch a number of times.

Great visuals but got lost trying to cram too many events into a single go. Really shows that they didn't have a cohesive story for the trilogy as a whole and were adhoc writing as they went. I'm glad it was JJ at the helm this time, you can tell what a fan he is.
A little fast but a solid way to end the saga. A lot of fun with a good amount of heart.

I really enjoyed Rise of Skywalker. No, it is not a great movie, but I found it to be a worthy and entertaining Star Wars movie. I saw the originals as a kid when I had an ability to overlook the fact that a band of rebels could really overcome an empire. Star Wars has always been about escapism, letting go, and enjoying a story of hope - a story that borders on impossible. For me, the Rise of Skywalker still captured that feeling. This movie absolutely could have been much better if it didn't have to course correct for The Last Jedi and try and squeeze too much into one film. Rian Johnson makes good films... I just don't think his Last Jedi Star Wars story fit the narrative for the Skywalker saga. I am happy with what JJ Abrams was able to put together considering what he had to work with.
coming off of the mistakes TLJ director, this one left some plot holes. but the TROS delivered bug beautiful action.
It's a great celebration of everything we love about Star Wars. This one was played for the fans, and it works. Join the party!

It was a mess. And I love every minute of it. :)
Things happened so fast and there's so many information... I will see it a couple of times in the following days in order to get my ideas in order.
It was a hell of a lot of fun and a little sad too.
Tons and tons of fan service.
"Professional" critics are gonna hate it because you know they always want every movie to be an art movie, but movie critics know nothing about what a Star Wars fan wants and J.J. Abrams delivers it good.

The movie was amazing and a great tribute to Star Wars fans that have been with the saga for a long time. It did have its flaws, as it felt a little rushed most of the time and did not have many surprises. However, Abrams did the best he could in an attempt to recover the trilogy from the Last Jedi. The battle sequences which filled a majority of the movie looked incredible. Overall, a great movie and a must see for all Star Wars fans.
